  "texts": [
    "The rows of the result table show the AP for different IOU values, such as: (a) 0.50:0.95: This is the mean AP over IOU thresholds from 0.50 to 0.95 with a step size of 0.05.",
    "This is the most comprehensive and robust metric, as it evaluates the model across a wide range of IOU values.",
    "(b) 0.50: This is the AP for an IOU threshold of 0.50, which is equivalent to the PASCAL VOC metric.",
    "This is a less strict metric, as it only requires a 50% overlap between the predicted and ground truth bounding boxes.",
    "(c) 0.75: This is the AP for the IOU threshold of 0.75, which is a stricter metric, as it requires a 75% overlap between the predicted and ground truth bounding boxes."
